{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\nGenerate `docs/cli-reference.md` from the CLI's OWN help data, so the command reference\ncannot drift, and gate it in CI like `scripts/gen_env_registry.py`.\n\n## Source of truth (verified — the CLI surface is two disjoint families)\n1. **50 help-backed subcommands** — enumerable programmatically:\n   - `rebar._cli._help.known_subcommands() -> frozenset[str]` (returns 50; it lists the\n     `*.txt` files under the `rebar._cli.help` package, one per subcommand).\n   - `rebar._cli._help.subcommand_help(sub) -> str|None` — the full usage text per command.\n   - `rebar._cli._help.overview() -> str` — `help/overview.txt`, whose rows carry each\n     command's one-line summary (the only source of the one-liners).\n2. **16 intercept-arm commands** — handled in `src/rebar/_cli/__init__.py` main() BEFORE the\n   `known_subcommands()` check (lines ~372-447), each owning its own `--help`, with NO\n   `help/*.txt` and NO overview row: `reconcile, review, review-code, scan-spec,\n   verify-completion, review-plan, sign-review, enrich, explain, verify-commit-ticket,\n   workflow, llm, jira-onboard, prompt, criteria, config`. These have no registry — the\n   generator carries this list explicitly and captures each via `rebar <cmd> --help`\n   (subprocess), and a drift check asserts the list still matches the `if argv[0] == \"...\"`\n   intercept ladder in `_cli/__init__.py` (so a newly-added intercept can't silently be\n   omitted).\n\nTotal ~66 commands. The generator MUST cover BOTH families (missing the intercepts would\ndrop review-plan/reconcile/workflow/etc. — the majority of the agent-facing surface).\n\n## Scope\n- Add `scripts/gen_cli_reference.py` (new): enumerate family 1 via `_help`, family 2 via\n  the explicit intercept list + `rebar <cmd> --help`; emit `docs/cli-reference.md` with a\n  \"Generated by … do not edit\" header (mirror `gen_env_registry.py`), grouped with the\n  50 help-backed commands (name + one-liner + usage) and the 16 intercept commands\n  (name + captured --help), each clearly labeled.\n- `--check` mode: regenerate in memory and exit non-zero if the committed file differs.\n- Robustness (implementation guidance, not a gated criterion): each `rebar <cmd> --help`\n  capture must check the subprocess exit code and non-empty output and raise/exit non-zero\n  on failure, so a broken intercept never emits a blank entry.\n- Wire a CI drift gate in `.github/workflows/test.yml` mirroring the env-registry gate\n  (run generator, `git diff --exit-code -- docs/cli-reference.md`, fail if stale).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `docs/cli-reference.md` is generated (marked generated) and lists BOTH families:\n      every `known_subcommands()` entry (50) AND all 16 intercept-arm commands.\n- [ ] Completeness proof (deterministic, prints nothing). The generator MUST render each\n      command name backtick-wrapped (e.g. `` `review` ``) so exact matching avoids\n      substring false-positives (`review` vs `review-plan`):\n      `python scripts/gen_cli_reference.py && for c in $(python -c \"from rebar._cli import _help; print(' '.join(sorted(_help.known_subcommands())))\"); do grep -qF \"\\`$c\\`\" docs/cli-reference.md || echo \"MISSING $c\"; done; for c in reconcile review review-code scan-spec verify-completion review-plan sign-review enrich explain verify-commit-ticket workflow llm jira-onboard prompt criteria config; do grep -qF \"\\`$c\\`\" docs/cli-reference.md || echo \"MISSING-INTERCEPT $c\"; done`\n- [ ] Drift gate works — a stale reference fails `--check` (deterministic, prints `CAUGHT`):\n      `python scripts/gen_cli_reference.py; printf '\\nstale\\n' >> docs/cli-reference.md; python scripts/gen_cli_reference.py --check >/dev/null 2>&1 && echo MISS || echo CAUGHT; python scripts/gen_cli_reference.py`\n- [ ] The generator's hardcoded intercept list matches the `if argv[0] == \"...\"` ladder\n      in `_cli/__init__.py` — DETERMINISTIC proof (prints nothing): a helper prints the\n      generator's intercept list and a grep-derived set of the ladder literals and diffs\n      them, e.g.\n      `python -c \"import ast,re,pathlib; src=pathlib.Path('src/rebar/_cli/__init__.py').read_text(); ladder=set(re.findall(r'argv\\[0\\]\\s*==\\s*\\\"([a-z-]+)\\\"', src)); import importlib.util as u; s=u.spec_from_file_location('g','scripts/gen_cli_reference.py'); m=u.module_from_spec(s); s.loader.exec_module(m); gen=set(m.INTERCEPT_COMMANDS); missing=ladder-gen; print('LADDER-NOT-IN-GEN:',sorted(missing)) if missing else None\"`\n      (the generator MUST expose its intercept list as `INTERCEPT_COMMANDS`; the ladder set\n      derived from the source must be a subset of it, so a newly-added intercept arm that\n      the generator forgot is caught).\n- [ ] The CI drift gate is actually wired in `.github/workflows/test.yml` (verify, prints\n      nothing): `grep -qF 'gen_cli_reference.py' .github/workflows/test.yml || echo \"GATE NOT WIRED\"`.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` stay green.\n\nFiles: `scripts/gen_cli_reference.py` (new), `docs/cli-reference.md` (new/generated),\n`.github/workflows/test.yml`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783825490285285001,"uuid":"e8d5a51c-fb09-429e-806c-6ece6968b0c8"}